{"id":"236589486_Upper-Bounding_the_k-Colorability_Threshold_by_Counting_Covers","abstract":"Let $G(n,m)$ be the random graph on $n$ vertices with $m$ edges. Let $d=2m/n$\nbe its average degree. We prove that $G(n,m)$ fails to be $k$-colorable with\nhigh probability if $d>2k\\ln k-\\ln k-1+o_k(1)$. This matches a conjecture put\nforward on the basis of sophisticated but non-rigorous statistical physics\nideas (Krzakala, Pagnani, Weigt 2004). The proof is based on applying the first\nmoment method to the number of \"covers\", a physics-inspired concept. By\ncomparison, a standard first moment over the number of $k$-colorings shows that\n$\\gnm$ is not $k$-colorable with high probability if $d>2k\\ln k-\\ln k$.","authors":["Amin Coja-Oghlan"],"meta":["May 2013The Electronic Journal of Combinatorics 20(3)","DOI:10.37236/3337","SourcearXiv"],"references":["236202777_Chasing_the_K-Colorability_Threshold","220342962_A_Note_on_the_Non-Colorability_Threshold_of_a_Random_Graph","45889775_Combinatorial_approach_to_the_interpolation_method_and_scaling_limits_insparse_random_graphs","10988252_Coloring_Random_Graphs","10962471_Random_graph_coloring_Statistical_physics_approach","6268915_Gibbs_States_and_the_Set_of_Solutions_of_Random_Constraint_Satisfaction_Problems","5915439_Phase_Transitions_in_the_Coloring_of_Random_Graphs","2735344_Where_really_hard_problems_are","1834814_Broken_Replica_Symmetry_Bounds_in_the_Mean_Field_Spin_Glass_Model","1738605_Statistical_Physics_of_Hard_Optimization_Problems","313609388_On_the_evolution_of_random_graphs","313429549_The_analysis_of_a_list-coloring_algorithm_on_a_random_graph","258873733_On_coloring_random_graphs","239761530_The_freezing_threshold_for_k-colourings_of_a_random_graph","227315806_The_chromatic_number_of_random_graphs","226558379_The_chromatic_number_of_random_graphs","226132597_Expose-and-merge_exploration_and_the_chromatic_number_of_a_random_graph","222837360_Almost_all_graphs_with_degree_4_are_3-colorable","222684514_On_the